Package com.nuix.javaenginesimple

Class EngineWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nuix.javaenginesimple.EngineWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class EngineWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
    This class provides convenience methods for getting a license and standing up the global container and engine instance. Caller must provide base directory of engine release they are running against. Once a license has been obtained, this will log a listing of features available on the license as well as information about the presence of third part dependencies that Nuix makes use of.

    • Method Detail

      • withDongleLicense

        public void withDongleLicense​(java.util.function.Consumer<nuix.Utilities> consumer)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Attempts to obtain a dongle based license. If and when a dongle based license is obtained, a Utilities object will be provided to consumer, which may then make use of the Nuix API to do work. Once the consumer has returned this method will cleanup the Engine and GlobalContainer instances it created.
        Parameters:
        consumer - Consumer which will make use of Utilities object once a license has been obtained.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - May throw exceptions due to: error creating GlobalContainer, error creating Engine instance or error obtaining license. Exceptions are caught locally, logged and then rethrown.
